@X-J-K-X wrote:

Okay, im back for more questions :P!.. I havent fixed my projectiles fully yet, but ill work on it as soon as its double hitting… Okay righht…

In server source - Project Destiny… There is a dark bow, and as the special, it hits twice… Exactly like a DDS… So i searched the VOID… And it said this…

if(IsAttacking && playerEquipment[playerWeapon] == 4827 && (misc.random(30) == 1))
         {
                int j = PlayerHandler.players[AttackingOn].absX;
                int k = PlayerHandler.players[AttackingOn].absY;
                int l = PlayerHandler.players[AttackingOn].playerLevel[playerHitpoints];
                SpecDamg(30);
                DDS2DAMG = true;
                DDStimer = 1;
                teleportToX = absX;
                teleportToY = absY;
                SpecialDelay -= 1;
         }
}

Sorry for any spelling mistakes, typed it up maself…
So… I changed

SpecDamg(30);

To…

SpecDamgg(30);

Because thats the name of my void… Also, i changed the names of the boolean to DDS2DAMG because it was already defined in client… So i changed DDS2DAMG to, DDS2DAMGG, and DDStimer, to DDStimerr…
Now… My problem… Is there a way so i can change this… To liek… Make it hit double “like spec”… But without the special attack? If so please do explain as fully as you can… I really am going to be disappointed if i get no posts after 2-3 weeks of work…
And please… Do not post “You need to add another void”… Or “Add this int, blaha blah”…

P.S… If you dont have anything helpful to say, im asking nicely. Please DO NOT post…
P.S.S… Do not flame me and spam up this topic if your talking aload of rubbish…

Thanks
